(613, 'Typhoid Fever', 'Typhoid fever is an acute bacterial infection caused by Salmonella typhi which enters the body through food and water contaminated by faeces from an infected individual. It is characterised by symptoms like fever, chills, rash called red spots on abdomen and chest, headache, ulceration of the intestinal wall and abdominal pain.', 'Typhoid fever.mp4', 'Paid', 'T'),
